      <h1>About me</h1>
      <p class="lead">I've been running Linux servers for over ten years. A passion became a profession. Today 35+ virtual machines and around 40 containers run on my own Proxmox cluster, behind a multi-tier segmented network, with encrypted, restore-tested backups. That is my own "data center in miniature", documented like a production environment. The simplest sentence about my work: <strong>what I offer, I run myself, every day.</strong></p>
    </section>

    <section data-section-key="weg">
      <h2>My path</h2>
      <p>It all started with curiosity, a server I wanted to understand rather than just use. The hobby turned into years of real practice: roles at IT service providers and system houses, and alongside them an operation of my own that has grown every year. I learn on real systems, not on slides.</p>
      <p>I'm formally completing that path right now: <strong>IHK-certified IT specialist for systems integration, degree expected by December 2026.</strong> I don't see the career switch as a gap but as a strength. I ran the systems before I held the certificate for them, and so I know how it feels when something breaks at night.</p>
      <ul class="facts">
        <li><strong>10+ years of hands-on Linux/server experience</strong>, 35+ VMs and ~40 containers in operation</li>
        <li>Hands-on experience at IT service providers and system houses</li>
        <li>IHK-certified IT specialist for <strong>systems integration</strong>, degree expected by December 2026</li>
        <li>Based in Ochsenhausen, Biberach district, on site for the region, international via remote support</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

